Syllabic nasals {{IPA|[m̩]}} and {{IPA|[n̩]}} also occur. Related to this is a phenomenon of [[prenasalized stop|prenasalization]], termed "[[anacrusis]]" by Sapir by analogy with the metrical term. It is probably best accounted for systematically by an underlying [[syllabic nasal]], since it occurs with some [[Approximant consonant|approximants]], as well as with voiced [[plosives]].

